## Report 

"The dataset's hardest and easiest race editions cluster almost entirely by course rather than by year: Boston accounts for 8 of the 10 hardest editions (driven by both extreme cold, as in 2018's 3.6°C with 11.2 m/s wind, and unusual heat, as in 2017 and 2021), while Chicago occupies all 10 of the easiest, most notably 2004 — near-ideal conditions of 9.6°C and just 1.1 m/s wind on the flattest course in the sample. This course-level clustering, rather than any clear trend over time, reinforces that structural course characteristics dominate year-to-year weather variation in determining overall race difficulty."

